const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;      // configurable
const server = app.listen(port, () => { /* ... */ });

// Graceful shutdown
process.on('SIGTERM', () => server.close(() => process.exit(0)));
process.on('unhandledRejection', (err) => { console.error(err); process.exit(1); });
```

### 7. Don't Start the Server on Require

`app.listen` runs as a side-effect of `require('./app')`, which breaks tests and tooling. Split into `app.js` (exports the app) and `server.js` (calls `listen`):

```js
