```
npm i helmet cors express-rate-limit zod pino pino-http
```

### Priority Order
1. Security middleware (helmet, cors, rate-limit, body limits) — highest ROI, lowest effort.
2. Centralized error handler + 404 handler.
3. Input validation scaffolding (even if no routes need it yet, wire up `zod`).
4. Config via env vars + graceful shutdown.
5. Structured logging + authentication before `/users` grows real data.

