### 1. No global error handling
If any route throws (sync or async), the default Express handler leaks stack traces. There's also no `process` handler for `uncaughtException` / `unhandledRejection`.

### 2. No input validation
`/users` doesn't take input today, but any future route (e.g., `/users/:id`, query filters) will need validation. Nothing is wired up.

### 3. Missing baseline security middleware
- No `helmet` (sets secure headers: CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, etc.)
- No rate limiting (DoS / brute-force exposure)
- No body-size limits on `express.json()`
- No CORS policy — either permissive by accident or unset
- `x-powered-by: Express` header is enabled by default (fingerprinting)

### 4. Hardcoded port, no graceful shutdown
`app.listen(3000)` ignores `process.env.PORT` and doesn't handle SIGTERM, so in-flight requests are dropped on deploy.

