  console.error({ msg: err.message, stack: err.stack, path: req.path });
  res.status(err.status || 500).json({ error: 'Internal Server Error' });
});
```
Never send `err.message` or `err.stack` to the client.

## 3. Process-level safety nets
Unhandled promise rejections and uncaught exceptions silently crash Node. Attach handlers so failures are logged and the process exits cleanly (so your supervisor — pm2/k8s — can restart):
```js
process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason) => { console.error(reason); process.exit(1); });
process.on('uncaughtException',  (err)    => { console.error(err);    process.exit(1); });
```

## 4. `app.listen` swallows errors
The callback form only fires on success. Capture `EADDRINUSE` / permission errors:
```js
