server.on('error', (err) => { console.error('Listen failed:', err); process.exit(1); });
```

## 5. Hardcoded port & no config validation
`3000` is baked in. Read from env and validate:
```js
const port = Number(process.env.PORT) || 3000;
if (!Number.isInteger(port) || port < 1 || port > 65535) {
  throw new Error(`Invalid PORT: ${process.env.PORT}`);
}
```

## 6. Body parsing is missing — but when you add it, set limits
The moment you add `app.use(express.json())`, cap payload size to prevent DoS via huge bodies:
```js
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: false, limit: '10kb' }));
```

## 7. Rate limiting
`/health` and `/users` are wide open. Add `express-rate-limit` (stricter on auth endpoints when you have them):
```js
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');
app.use(rateLimit({ windowMs: 60_000, max: 100, standardHeaders: true, legacyHeaders: false }));
