  if (!Number.isInteger(id) || id <= 0) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid user id' });
  }
  ```
- Never pass user input directly into DB queries, shell commands, filesystem paths, or template strings.

## 3. Security hardening

| Concern | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| Missing security headers | `app.use(require('helmet')())` |
| No rate limiting | `express-rate-limit` on public endpoints |
| CORS unconfigured | `cors({ origin: <allowlist> })` — don't use `*` if auth is added later |
| Leaking PII in `/users` | Emails shouldn't be returned unauthenticated; add authn/authz before exposing user data |
| Hardcoded port | Use `process.env.PORT` with a validated fallback |
| `x-powered-by` header | `app.disable('x-powered-by')` (helmet does this too) |
| No HTTPS / TLS termination | Terminate TLS at a proxy (nginx, ALB) and set `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` |
| Logging | Use `pino` or `morgan`; never log secrets, tokens, or full request bodies |

